            <div class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Line Counter (Go)</div>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-base">
                This utility was motivated by my desire to learn Go. I was reflecting on <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unix_philosophy">The Unix Philosophy</a> and it struck me that `wc` (a command-line utility that can count words, characters, and lines)
                would be interesting to replace. But, unlike `wc`, I would only do one thing. Count lines. In writing my own utility, I could learn how to read input from the command line and also how to read a file in Go.
            </p>
