            <p class="text-gray-700 text-base mb-6">
                Right around the time that I finished my <a href="https://github.com/hyrmn/lc">Go-based line counter</a>, a Twitter storm solidified with strong opinions on how ill-suited .NET was for system utilities. That it
                was slow, etc. 
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-base mb-6">
                While much of my daily work revolved around .NET Full Framework, I wanted to learn more about .NET Core (the cross-platform, leaner, meaner, newer scion in Microsoft). What better way to learn than, well, re-writing
                something that would give me a comparison. 
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-base">
                The most surprising thing to me is how similar the code looks between the two. Of course, that stands to reason as I wrote them both. But, I tried to be idiomatic with each language. (and, spoiler, they were virtually tied on speed)
